casebody.data:
Lonnie SNELLING, Appellant,
v.
Patrick J. KENNY, et al., Respondents. No. ED 105619 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION TWO. FILED: December 26, 2017
Motion for Rehearing and/or Transfer to Supreme Court Denied February 26, 2018
Application for Transfer Denied May 1, 2018 FOR APPELLANT: Lonnie Snelling, 1518-79 th Street, St. Louis, MO 63130. For Respondent: Matthew S. Chase, 231 South Bemiston Ave. Suite 800, Clayton, MO 63105, Kara Dyan Krawzik, 7701 Forsyth Blvd., Suite 800, St. Louis, MO 63105. Before Lisa P. Page, P.J., Roy L. Richter, J., and Philip M. Hess, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM

Lonnie Snelling ("Appellant") appeals from the trial court's March 2, 2017 judgment granting Appellant's motion to set aside the judgment entered in favor of J.D. Haynes ("Respondent") and dismissing all claims against Respondent with prejudice, and the trial court's May 27, 2014 judgment dismissing Appellant's Second Amended Petition.

After review of Appellant's brief and the record on appeal, we find no error of law. The judgment of the trial court is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
